        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/mounting-deaths-aid-warnings-ignored.jpg" alt="Despite the mounting death toll and warnings from aid organizations, Israel has resisted calls for a broader change in polic" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #a9a7af">
            <i>Despite the mounting death toll and warnings from aid organizations, Israel has resisted calls for a broader change in policy. Credits: AP Photo</i>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
           <strong>The what:</strong> Humanitarian <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-28-jul-25-spotlight-h1-1-aid-will-enter-gaza-from-egypt" target="_blank">aid will enter Gaza from Egypt</a> after months of international pressure and warnings from relief agencies. Israel announced the establishment of ‚Äúhumanitarian corridors‚Äù and daily pauses in fighting in Al-Mawasi, Deir al-Balah, and Gaza City, from 10 a.m. to 8 p.m. local time, to ensure the safer delivery of aid. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
         <strong>The why:</strong> Global leaders condemned Israel‚Äôs halt of humanitarian aid and its controversial distribution system, which has intensified hunger. Humanitarian agencies say that one-third of the population lacked a gateway to food for multiple days. Israel blamed Hamas for intercepting goods, but their allies pushed back, insisting that military concerns cannot justify mass starvation. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
           <strong>The concern:</strong> Malnutrition has sharply increased, especially among children. In Gaza City, one in five children under five is acutely malnourished. Seventy-four people have died this year from starvation, including 38 adults. Doctors warn that many children may suffer <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-28-jul-25-spotlight-h1-2-irreversible-damage" target="_blank">irreversible damage</a> due to prolonged lack of food. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
           Read the full report by the World Health Organization <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-28-jul-25-spotlight-h1-3-here" target="_blank">here</a>.
          </p>
