        </mj-text> 
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>
            Summary: Taiwan voted against the ousting of the opposition lawmakers amid China‚Äôs interference assertions. </strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
         <strong>The what:</strong> Taiwanese voters rejected the ruling party‚Äôs (DDP) bid to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-28-jul-25-spotlight-h2-4-oust-24-china-friendly-opposition-party" target="_blank">oust 24 China-friendly opposition party</a> (KMT) lawmakers. The DPP party accepted the defeat but emphasized the importance of resisting Chinese influence. China's Taiwan Affairs Office celebrated the vote, calling it a victory against ‚Äúpolitical manipulation‚Äù by the DDP. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          <strong>The context:</strong> The DDP party has accused KMT lawmakers of blocking legislation, particularly the defense budget, and pushing pro-China changes. Another round of similar elections is scheduled for August 23, which will determine the fate of seven KMT lawmakers. To take legislative control, DDP must oust six KMT lawmakers and secure the following by-elections. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          <strong>The big picture:</strong> Taiwan's Mainland Affairs Council says it has evidence of <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-28-jul-25-spotlight-h2-5-china-s-interference-in-its-elections" target="_blank">China‚Äôs interference in its elections</a>. China has branded Taiwan‚Äôs president as a separatist and has increased military pressure in recent months, as it views Taiwan as part of Chinese territory. Meanwhile, Taiwan is facing a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-28-jul-25-spotlight-h2-6-political-gridlock" target="_blank">political gridlock</a> over major legislative decisions, which restricts its ability to push forward the necessary agenda. 
          </p>
        </mj-text>
